IPFS powers the Distributed WebIPFS为分布式网络提供动力

A peer-to-peer hypermedia protocol 一个点对点的超媒体协议
designed to preserve and grow humanity's knowledge 旨在保护和增长人类的知识
by making the web upgradeable, resilient, and more open. 使网络可升级、有弹性、更开放。

Get started 开始吧 How it works 它是如何工作的

The web of tomorrow needs IPFS today明天的网络需要今天的IPFS

IPFS aims to complement HTTP in order to build a better web for all of us. IPFS旨在补充HTTP，以便为我们所有人建立一个更好的网络。

Today's web is inefficient and expensive 今天的网络是低效和昂贵的

HTTP downloads files from one server at a time — but peer-to-peer IPFS retrieves pieces from multiple nodes at once, enabling substantial bandwidth savings. IPFS makes it possible to efficiently distribute high volumes of data without duplication. HTTP每次从一台服务器上下载文件--但对等的IPFS一次从多个节点上检索文件，可以大大节省带宽。IPFS使得有效地分发大量数据而不重复成为可能。

Today's web can't preserve humanity's history 今天的网络无法保存人类的历史

The average lifespan of a web page is 100 days before it's gone forever. The medium of our era shouldn't be this fragile. IPFS makes it simple to set up resilient networks for mirroring data, and thanks to content addressing, files stored using IPFS are automatically versioned. 一个网页的平均寿命是100天，然后就永远消失了。我们这个时代的媒介不应该是如此脆弱的。IPFS使得建立有弹性的网络来镜像数据变得简单，而且由于内容寻址，使用IPFS存储的文件会自动进行版本管理。

Today's web is centralized, limiting opportunity 今天的网络是集中式的，限制了机会

The Internet has turbocharged innovation by being one of the great equalizers in human history — but increasing consolidation of control threatens that progress. IPFS stays true to the original vision of an open, flat web by delivering technology to make that vision a reality. 互联网是人类历史上最伟大的平等者之一，从而加速了创新--但控制权的日益巩固威胁着这种进步。IPFS通过提供技术使这一愿景成为现实，从而忠实于开放、扁平的网络的最初愿景。

Today's web is addicted to the backbone 今天的网络沉迷于骨干网

IPFS powers the creation of diversely resilient networks that enable persistent availability — with or without internet backbone connectivity. This means better connectivity for the developing world, during natural disasters, or just when you're on flaky coffee shop wi-fi. IPFS为创建多样化的弹性网络提供动力，无论是否有互联网骨干连接，都能实现持久的可用性。这意味着在发展中国家，在自然灾害期间，或者当你在咖啡店使用不稳定的Wi-Fi时，有更好的连接。

How IPFS worksIPFS如何工作

Here's what happens when you add a file to IPFS — whether you're storing that file on your own local node or one operated by a pinning service or IPFS-enabled app. 以下是当你向IPFS添加文件时发生的事情--无论你是将文件存储在你自己的本地节点上，还是由钉子服务或支持IPFS的应用程序操作的节点上。

When you add a file to IPFS, your file is split into smaller chunks, cryptographically hashed, and given a unique fingerprint called a content identifier (CID). This CID acts as a permanent record of your file as it exists at that point in time. 当你向IPFS添加文件时，你的文件被分割成小块，经过加密散列，并被赋予一个独特的指纹，称为内容标识符（CID）。这个CID作为你的文件的永久记录，因为它存在于那个时间点上。

When other nodes look up your file, they ask their peer nodes who's storing the content referenced by the file's CID. When they view or download your file, they cache a copy — and become another provider of your content until their cache is cleared. 当其他节点查询你的文件时，他们会询问他们的对等节点谁在存储文件的CID所引用的内容。当他们查看或下载你的文件时，他们会缓存一个副本--成为你内容的另一个提供者，直到他们的缓存被清除。

A node can pin content in order to keep (and provide) it forever, or discard content it hasn't used in a while to save space. This means each node in the network stores only content it is interested in, plus some indexing information that helps figure out which node is storing what. 一个节点可以钉住内容，以便永远保留（和提供）它，或者丢弃它有一段时间没有使用的内容，以节省空间。这意味着网络中的每个节点只存储它感兴趣的内容，再加上一些索引信息，帮助找出哪个节点在存储什么。

If you add a new version of your file to IPFS, its cryptographic hash is different, and so it gets a new CID. This means files stored on IPFS are resistant to tampering and censorship — any changes to a file don't overwrite the original, and common chunks across files can be reused in order to minimize storage costs. 如果你在IPFS上添加一个新版本的文件，它的加密哈希值是不同的，因此它得到一个新的CID。这意味着存储在IPFS上的文件可以抵御篡改和审查--对文件的任何修改都不会覆盖原始文件，而且不同文件的共同块可以重复使用，以尽量减少存储成本。

However, this doesn't mean you need to remember a long string of CIDs — IPFS can find the latest version of your file using the IPNS decentralized naming system, and DNSLink can be used to map CIDs to human-readable DNS names. 然而，这并不意味着你需要记住一长串的CIDs--IPFS可以使用IPNS分散的命名系统找到你的文件的最新版本，并且可以使用DNSLink将CIDs映射到人类可读的DNS名称。

IPFS can help here and nowIPFS可以在这里和现在提供帮助

No matter what you do with the web, IPFS helps make it better today. 无论你用网络做什么，IPFS都能帮助你今天做得更好。

Archivists 档案员

Storing archival data using IPFS enables deduplication, clustered persistence, and high performance — empowering you to store the world's information for future generations. 使用IPFS存储档案数据可以实现重复数据删除、集群持久性和高性能--使你能够为后代存储世界信息。

Service providers 服务提供商

Providing large amounts of data to users? Storing on IPFS could help you slash bandwidth costs thanks to its use of secure, peer-to-peer content delivery. 向用户提供大量的数据？在IPFS上存储可以帮助你削减带宽成本，因为它使用了安全的、点对点的内容传输。

Researchers 研究人员

If you're working with or distributing large datasets, storing that data using IPFS can help speed up performance and unlock decentralized archiving. 如果你正在处理或分发大型数据集，使用IPFS存储这些数据可以帮助加快性能，并解锁分散的归档。

Blockchain developers 区块链开发者

IPFS content addressing enables you to store large files off-chain and put immutable, permanent links in transactions — timestamping and securing content without having to put the data itself on-chain. IPFS内容寻址使您能够在链外存储大型文件，并在交易中放入不可变的永久链接--对内容进行时间标记和安全保护，而不必将数据本身放在链上。

Content creators 内容创建者

IPFS empowers creators to build and share on the decentralized web — whether that's delivering content free from intermediary control or minting NFTs that stand the test of time. IPFS使创作者能够在去中心化的网络上建立和分享--无论是提供不受中介控制的内容还是铸造经得起时间考验的NFT。

Offline users 离线用户

High-latency networks cause major obstacles for those with poor internet infrastructure. Peer-to-peer IPFS offers resilient access to data independent of latency or backbone connectivity. 高延迟的网络给那些互联网基础设施差的人带来了重大障碍。对等的IPFS提供了对数据的弹性访问，不受延迟或骨干连接的影响。
